Introduction to DFT (Kohn Sham) :
- solving many body schrodinger's equations
- Self Consistent: initial guess (density)-potential energy values- solve eqns-wave fns- new density values
- 
Input: Creating a Mole Object: 
(Solvation Model)
- define atomic structure- Hellman Feyman Vibrations are used. 
- Define Integral gradient 

mol = pyscf.M(
    atom = 'H 0 0 0; F 0 0 1.1',  # in Angstrom
    basis = '631g',
    symmetry = True,
)

Periodic Boundary Conditions and Exchange Correlation Functional (xc)
mf = mol.KS() #Kohn-Sham (instance of dft class)
mf.xc = 'pbe'
mf.kernel()

#analyze ground state energies and muliken charges
mf.analyze() 
